properties.description: Grade II-listed Georgian domestic building c.1760, formerly part of Bedford Estate. Interior refurbished 1924-5 to form lecture hall (restored 2014), library, bookshop and offices. Oak woodwork and green Doulton tiles line the staircase.

images.title: Bust of Swedenborg by Preston Powers (1879)
Stained glass window image of Swedenborg, vestibule (detail)

properties.name: The Swedenborg Society

properties.description: A rare example of Thomas Archer's work and a masterpiece of English Baroque, originally dubbed Queen Anne's Footstool. A Grade I listed building, restored by Marshall Sisson after extensive bombing damage, now a busy concert hall.

images.title: St John's Smith Square: Building Detail
St John's Smith Square: Building Detail
The East Side of the Square

properties.name: St John's Smith Square

properties.description:
Grade I listed Georgian church on the Thames. St Marys has outstanding interior and monuments; commemorating those associated with the church: Painter Turner, poet William Blake, botanist William Curtis and Benedict Arnold. 
St Marys is hosting an Open House Week Floral Festival with arrangements and installations by local and international florists, as well as displays of historical documents.
properties.name: St Mary's Church, Battersea

properties.description: St Anne's Limehouse has been described as 'the finest parish church in England.' Designed by Nicholas Hawksmoor, it is Grade I listed and one of the Major Churches in the Church of England. It is home to a thriving Christian congregation.
properties.name: St Anne's Church, Limehouse

properties.description: Loughborough Pearson's red brick building is unimposing from the outside, but inside is a riot of Gothic Revival design. Golden mosaics reveal the character of the Grade II* listed chapel, built as part of the Middlesex Hospital.

images.title: The ornate baptisery of the Fitzrovia Chapel

properties.name: Fitzrovia Chapel

properties.description: Wren designed building of 1675, interior lost in blitz of 1940, reopened 1957 with 'Wren inspired' interior
properties.name: St Bride's Church, Fleet Street

properties.description: A guided walk through Home Park Water Meadows with Thames Landscape Strategy. It is the site of a wetland restoration project that has increased biodiversity and sustainability on the historic site. It is not usually open to the public.
properties.name: Flood Meadows at Hampton Court

properties.description: Our timber frame building was designed by Matrix Feminist Design Co-Operative, and built by women. It represents our community's history of activism-the same ethos that transformed our site from dereliction, into a thriving community garden

images.title: Carpenter Louise Heaps working on the building's frame
Louise Heaps (lead carpenter, left) working on the portal frames for the building

properties.name: Walworth Garden

properties.description:
A great little museum set in the Grade 2 listed Ossulston Estate - a prime example of pre-war Social housing - based on Karl Marz Hof in Vienna.
Open Tuesday to Friday 9am-5pm, plus Saturday 14th, Saturday 21st and Sunday 22nd September 11am-4pm.

images.title: A museum on the social housing Ossulston Estate - a Space for us?
Pearly Queen outside the People's Museum
Hear the story of stolen social housing art from those who restituted it. Gilbert Bayes 'Draper'

properties.name: People's Museum Somers Town

properties.description: Start Stamford Brook tube.  Follow the hidden river, Stamford Brook, through streets and parks.  Amongst the architecture we will see on this route is a delightful square with great variety.  Finish near Hammersmith Station .

images.title: Map of course of Stamford Brook

properties.name: Stamford Brook walk

properties.description:
Andaz London Liverpool Street, a concept by Hyatt, blends rich history dating back to the 1200s with modern decor and the vibrant energy of its London neighborhood.

Step inside and join us for an open house tour led by our dedicated team!
properties.name: Andaz London Liverpool Street

properties.description:
A walking tour exploring the 1930s art deco and modernist architecture of Hampstead Garden Suburb, led by Joe Mathieson of the Hampstead Garden Suburb Trust. 

1 of 3 walks run by the Trust.
properties.name: Streamline in the Suburb

properties.description:
A 2.5 hour walking tour showcasing unexpected and hidden architectural landmarks of the South Bank area, revealing the different ways in which spaces have been reclaimed, reused and revived. 

Two walks held on two dates following a route from Lambeth Palace and the Garden Museum to Bernie Spain Gardens. Two walks held on two dates.

Lambeth Palace Library.  Photo by Lambeth Palace Library
Feliks Topolski's studio in South Bank. Photo by South Bank London

properties.name: Lost & Hidden Architecture of South Bank Walk

properties.description: A floating acoustic architecture, playfully reframing public space as an essential community engagement through sound & site mapping. Accessed by smartphone, headphones & echoes.xyz app, the Pavilion is located outside the Serpentine Gallery,. Drawing on Oskar & Zofia Hansen’s Open Form architectural concept it is one of 15 in a series including Venice, Berlin, Dublin, Bergen and Arctic Norway.

images.title: Architectural and spatial design functions also as logo for London Pavilion audiowork
QR code to access London Open Form Pavilion of Air
Architectural design & spatial sound design for Pavilion with position in Kensington Gardens

properties.name: London Open Form Pavilion of Air

properties.description: Public Tours tours by Architect's DSDHA and the team at National Youth Theatre of the NYT's recently redeveloped RIBA-award-winning building, which created the UK's first theatre dedicated to staging work created by young people. This project is supported by the Mayor of London.

National Youth Theatre Photo by Jim Stephenson

properties.description: A 3-hour walking tour based around Royal Albert Dock that takes in architecture including London City Airport, The Tate & Lyle Sugar Refinery and the much politicised Royal Albert Dock development with some unexpected stop offs along the way.

images.title: Join a walking tour to discover the waterfront developments and history of Royal Albert Dock

properties.name: Sugar and spice and all things nice - a sensory inspired walk

properties.description: Guided walking tours of the grounds of Bethlem Royal Hospital, taking in the Hospital's historic Chapel, its beautiful grounds, Bethlem Museum of the Mind, and Bethlem Gallery.
properties.name: Bethlem Royal Hospital

properties.description: A Grade II Listed building of special architectural and historic interest, it originated at the end of the 19th century, during which Walthamstow was transformed from a rural community to a bustling suburb of “London over the border".
properties.name: Walthamstow Central library

properties.description: Art Deco building designed in 1934 by Leslie Kemp and Tasker in International Moderne style. Now the temporary home of West Wickham Library.
properties.name: West Wickham Library

properties.description: We have been collecting objects about the history of Brent for over 50 years. Visitors can find out about an Eiffel tower in Wembley, why you might make a pilgrimage to Willesden and what the Victorian streets of Brent were really like.
properties.name: Brent Museum

properties.description: Since 2000, Serpentine has invited internationally renowned and emerging architects to create their first completed structure in England. In 2024, Minsuk Cho, Mass Studies has designed the Serpentine Pavilion. Titled Archipelagic Void, the Pavilion is composed of five ‘islands’, each structure is unique in size, height and form.

images.title: Serpentine Pavilion 2024 designed by Minsuk Cho, Mass Studies. Design render, exterior view. Photo ©
Serpentine Pavilion 2024 designed by Minsuk Cho, Mass Studies. Design render, exterior view. Photo ©

properties.name: Serpentine Pavilion 2024

properties.description:
Shaftesbury Hall is a Tin Tabernacle  rebuilt by North London Samaritans in 2018 to replicate the original Hall built in the 1890s.
It has been owned by North London Samaritans for 50 years and since the rebuild is used as a Community Hub, with our branch of Samaritans at the rear.
properties.name: Shaftesbury Hall

properties.description:
The Little Ship Club is a yacht club for sailors, motorboaters, and non-sailors alike.

Our beautiful clubhouse is right on the Thames by Southwark Bridge in London. If members aren't on the sea, they are in the club, enjoying good company, excellent food, and a great social calendar.
properties.name: Little Ship Club

properties.description: From Red Lion to Soho- a walk through old Holborn.
properties.name: Four Squares tour

properties.description:
Explore Christ Church, a Grade II George Bains art nouveau/gothic style church. Activities for families include a treasure trail, games and crafts and cream teas available.
Sat 14 Sept: Open 10am-3pm. 2pm Lecture on George Bains by Andrew Scott, FREE
Friday 20 Sept: 7-9.30pm Concert with Life and mission choir, FREE
properties.name: Christ Church New Southgate and Friern Barnet

properties.description: We are a theatre company for performers and artists with learning disabilities in the West London area.  We will screen a free immersive experience, run on a loop, entitled Red Rope. It tells a powerful story about the impact of plastic on our oceans and features artworks, dance, music and poetry by our performers and artists. We will also display works of art.

images.title: Red Rope immersive experience in our Studio Theatre

properties.name: IMPACT Community Arts Centre
